                                "byte_start": 88611,
                                "byte_stop": 128526,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has the opinion in 04-1371, Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner \u0026 Smith versus Dabit."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.958,
                        "stop": 297.012,
                        "byte_start": 128526,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.958,
                                "stop": 15.918,
                                "byte_start": 128526,
                                "byte_stop": 152350,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the 2nd Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.918,
                                "stop": 33.053,
                                "byte_start": 152350,
                                "byte_stop": 220895,
                                "text": "We granted review to resolve a conflict between the 2nd and 7th Circuits over the extent to which the Securities Litigation Uniform Standards Act of 1998 preempts plaintiffs from bringing certain class actions under state law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.053,
                                "stop": 52.74,
                                "byte_start": 220895,
                                "byte_stop": 299576,
                                "text": "The respondent in this case is a former Merrill Lynch broker who brought a class action under Oklahoma law, alleging that Merrill Lynch had breached state-law duties that it owed to its brokers by disseminating research, misleading research and thereby manipulating stock prices."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.74,
                                "stop": 66.481,
                                "byte_start": 299576,
                                "byte_stop": 354538,
                                "text": "His complaint encompassed what are known as holder claims, claims that the brokers were injured because they continued to hold their stocks long beyond the point when, had the truth been known, they would have sold."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.481,
                                "stop": 78.273,
                                "byte_start": 354538,
                                "byte_stop": 401767,
                                "text": "These holder claims are different from claims brought by purchasers or sellers alleging a particular transaction of purchase or sale was wrongfully induced."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.273,
                                "stop": 103.849,
                                "byte_start": 401767,
                                "byte_stop": 504062,
                                "text": "The Federal District Court dismissed the case, concluding that it was preempted by the 1998 Act, which provides that no covered class action based upon state law and alleging a misrepresentation or omission of a material fact in connection with the purchase or sale of a covered security may be maintained in any state or federal court by any private party."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.849,
                                "stop": 117.699,
                                "byte_start": 504062,
                                "byte_stop": 559442,
                                "text": "On appeal however, the 2nd Circuit reached a different conclusion, reasoning that holder claims are not, \u201cin connection with the purchase or sale\u201d, of a security within the meaning of the 1998 Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.699,
                                "stop": 128.944,
                                "byte_start": 559442,
                                "byte_stop": 604477,
                                "text": "The Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and SEC Rule 10b-5 generally prohibit fraud in connection with the purchase or sale of a security."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.944,
                                "stop": 145.07,
                                "byte_start": 604477,
                                "byte_stop": 668947,
                                "text": "Ever since 1946, federal courts have recognized a private federal cause of action for damages for violations of Rule 10b-5, but we have held that only purchasers or sellers may invoke that remedy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.07,
                                "stop": 151.277,
                                "byte_start": 668947,
                                "byte_stop": 693816,
                                "text": "Thus, respondent in this case does not have a federal remedy for his alleged injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.277,
                                "stop": 168.87,
                                "byte_start": 693816,
                                "byte_stop": 764138,
                                "text": "On the other hand, in enforcement actions initiated by the SEC, we have broadly construed the \u201cin connection with\u201d phrase to encompass a variety of situations in which investors other than actual purchasers or sellers are the injured parties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.87,
                                "stop": 183.803,
                                "byte_start": 764138,
                                "byte_stop": 823906,
                                "text": "The 1998 Act that we construe today broadly preempts a large category of class actions that are based on state law and allege fraud in connection with the purchase or sale of a security."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.803,
                                "stop": 201.887,
                                "byte_start": 823906,
                                "byte_stop": 896213,
                                "text": "The question for decision, then, is whether the act only preempts state law class actions for which federal law provides a remedy, as the 2nd Circuit held, or whether, as the 7th Circuit has held, it also preempts state-law class actions for which there is no federal remedy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.887,
                                "stop": 214.714,
                                "byte_start": 896213,
                                "byte_stop": 947517,
                                "text": "We conclude that the broad interpretation of the \u201cin connection with\u201d phrase that we have accepted in SEC enforcement actions is the meaning that Congress intended in the 1998 Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.714,
                                "stop": 243.459,
                                "byte_start": 947517,
                                "byte_stop": 1062456,
                                "text": "This conclusion is supported not only by the statute\u2019s text, but also by the concerns that led to its enactment; namely, that Congress believed that lawyers who were bringing securities class actions in state court were invoking their state remedies to avoid the necessity of complying with an earlier federal statute that had tightened the requirements for bringing securities class actions under federal law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.459,
                                "stop": 264.771,
                                "byte_start": 1062456,
                                "byte_stop": 1147720,
                                "text": "Our conclusion is consistent with the presumption that Congress does not cavalierly preempt state law causes of action, because the 1998 Act does not actually preempt any cause of action, but rather merely denies plaintiffs the right to use the class-action device to vindicate a carefully defined category of claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.771,
                                "stop": 274.262,
                                "byte_start": 1147720,
                                "byte_stop": 1185754,
                                "text": "Moreover, it is federal law rather than state law that has long provided the principle basis for asserting class-action securities-fraud acclaims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 274.262,
                                "stop": 282.429,
                                "byte_start": 1185754,
                                "byte_stop": 1218355,
                                "text": "Thus, this is by no means a case in which a federal statute has eliminated a historically entrenched state-law remedy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 282.429,
                                "stop": 292.126,
                                "byte_start": 1218355,
                                "byte_stop": 1257120,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we vacate the judgment of the Court of Appeals for the 2nd Circuit and remand for further proceedings consistent with our unanimous opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 292.126,
                                "stop": 297.012,
                                "byte_start": 1257120,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito did not participate in the consideration or decision of the case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
